Because tree growth and mortality are determinants of forest population dynamics60,68, they can be used to characterise its ecosystem state in response to extreme climate events when recruitment is controlled for. For each measurement period t from 2001 to 2017, we use DBH of each tree to construct its stem basal area increment and then sum all trees in a plot P. This basal area growth rate for plot P at time t, BAGRP,t (in cm²), is an indicator of plot-level performance:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
